<exercise checkit-seed="0016" checkit-slug="A2" checkit-title="Standard matrices">
  <statement>
    <ol>
      <li>Find the standard matrix for the linear transformation <m>S:\mathbb{R}^ 3  \to \mathbb{R}^ 4 </m> given by
              <me>S\left(  \left[\begin{array}{c}
x \\
y \\
z
\end{array}\right]  \right) =  \left[\begin{array}{c}
3 \, x - 4 \, y - 5 \, z \\
-2 \, x + y + 5 \, z \\
-y + 6 \, z \\
x - 2 \, y
\end{array}\right] .</me></li>
      <li>Let <m>T:\mathbb{R}^ 3  \to \mathbb{R}^ 3 </m> be the linear transformation given by the standard matrix
              <me> \left[\begin{array}{ccc}
-2 &amp; -1 &amp; -1 \\
1 &amp; 0 &amp; -2 \\
-1 &amp; 0 &amp; 3
\end{array}\right] .</me>
              Compute <m>T\left( \left[\begin{array}{c}
-2 \\
-1 \\
0
\end{array}\right]  \right)</m>.
          </li>
    </ol>
  </statement>
  <answer>
    <ol>
      <li>
        <me> \left[\begin{array}{ccc}
3 &amp; -4 &amp; -5 \\
-2 &amp; 1 &amp; 5 \\
0 &amp; -1 &amp; 6 \\
1 &amp; -2 &amp; 0
\end{array}\right] </me>
      </li>
      <li>
        <me>T\left( \left[\begin{array}{c}
-2 \\
-1 \\
0
\end{array}\right]  \right)= \left[\begin{array}{c}
5 \\
-2 \\
2
\end{array}\right] </me>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </answer>
</exercise>

